<h2>FAQ deep dives</h2>
<p><strong>Browse vs cart recovery difference?</strong> Browse is lower intent — proof-first, lighter incentive, longer education. Cart gets urgency and tiered recovery. Never duplicate offers same day. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Discount on browse email one?</strong> Avoid on consideration categories. Proof and education first. Incentive email three for cold segment only if policy allows. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
<p><strong>Best tools for browse abandonment?</strong> Sequenzy execution, Klaviyo depth scoring, Yotpo proof, Privy collision awareness. Stack operators should document this answer in internal runbooks — not rely on tribal knowledge when agencies turn over.</p>
